I didnt change any rules/code.
Even just replaced the addDefaultProvider() for default:
```php
namespace App\Validation;

use Cake\Validation\Validation as CoreValidation;
use PhpCollective\DecimalObject\Decimal;

class Validation extends CoreValidation {

	public static function decimal(mixed $check, int|bool|null $places = null, ?string $regex = null): bool {
		return parent::decimal($check, $places, $regex);
	}

}
```
is the exact same signature

and the validation rule is also the same as before:

		$validator
			->decimal('tax');

This would not work unfortunately.
It now also screws up other validation methods/fields:
```
Unable to call method `isScalar` in `default` provider for field `id`
```

Something really wacky is going on. I am running just this test https://github.com/cakephp/cakephp/blob/e15d186e05e9e02231d53ba3bb6daa9290c3a470/tests/TestCase/Validation/ValidatorTest.php#L2347 and sure enough as this point https://github.com/cakephp/cakephp/blob/e15d186e05e9e02231d53ba3bb6daa9290c3a470/src/Validation/ValidationRule.php#L145 the `$args` array is 
```
[
  (int) 0 => (float) 10.1,
  (int) 1 => (int) 2,
  (int) 2 => [
    'newRecord' => true,
    'data' => [
      'username' => (float) 10.1
    ],
    'field' => 'username',
    'providers' => [
      'default' => object(Cake\Validation\RulesProvider) id:0 {
        [protected] _class => 'Cake\Validation\Validation'
        [protected] _reflection => object(ReflectionClass) id:1 {
          name => 'Cake\Validation\Validation'
        }
      }
    ]
  ]
]
```

But a `debug(func_get_args());` in `Validation::decimal()` gives
```
[
  (int) 0 => (float) 10.1,
  (int) 1 => (int) 2
]
```

The 3rd array value of `$args` vanishes! Does PHP auto skip the value due to type mismatch?  And if so why does the error show up only when you extend `Validation`?
